      • f

        public String f(String u,
                int t)
        If t is less than the length of u, then return the substring of u beginning at 1 + t; Otherwise, return an empty string. It is assumed that u and v are not null.
        Parameters:
        u - String to slice
        t - Lower bound of the index at which to slice u
        Returns:
        The substring of u beginning at index, 1 + t, if t is less than the length of u, or an empty string otherwise.
